
WOrdCount you know you want it
===
```
sh enter_tiny_container.sh
export HADOOP_CONFIG_DIR=/compositions/simple-fullstack/hd_conf/
/opt/hadoop/bin/hadoop jar /opt/hadoop/share/hadoop/mapreduce/hadoop-mapreduce-examples-3.4.2.jar wordcount hdfs://nn1:8020/tmp/README /tmp/out
```

K8S
===
If you have built your configuration in such a way that it is sharable across all nodes. This is a nice recipe:
```
minikube kubectl create configmap hd_conf --from-file=hd_conf --dry-run=client -o yaml

countainers:
...
volumeMounts:
  - name: config-volume
    mountPath: /hd_conf
    readOnly: true
volumes:
  - name : config-volume
    configMap:
      name: hd_config
```


